0.cdata!:
EVALUATION DU PROJET PORTUAIRE DE JIJEL
            - ALGERIE

abstracts.cdata!:
The proposed project is primarily the
            construction of a new port at Jijel, plus technical
            assistance. It consists of the following elements: (a) Civil
            Works: (i) construction of breakwaters, berths, transit
            sheds and supporting facilities; (ii) dredging and
            reclamation; (iii) paving of roads and storage areas; (b)
            Cargo handling equipment. (c) Consultants Services for: (i)
            project design, preparation of tender documents and
            construction supervision; (ii) technical assistance for
            improving port planning, management, administration and
            operations, and training; (iii) technical assistance for
            studies and preparation of a new port accounting system and
            tariff structure; (d) Provision of port construction equipment.
